              |                    |                    |
feb. 14 1995  | Repaired a booboo. I used sys:rexxc/rx in the programs to get
              | the scripts executed. If users moved their rexxc dir contents
              | to C: there is a problem. Now I just use 'rx'.
              |                    |                    |
feb. 25 1995  | Swapped <UL> and <OL> tags around as they had been tied into
              | the wrong entries.                            
              |                    |                    |
feb. 26 1995  | Added HTML-Wizard to the suite. Thus making it a foursome...             
              |                                               
feb. 27 1995  | Built in an ARexx host into all 4 programs...
              |                                             
mar.  9 1995  | Added the RXPATH tooltype and made the programs default to 
              | SYS:Rexxc/ if started from their icons. As it turned out the
              | SYS:rexxc/ path isn't in the workbench path 100%. Resulting
              | in some weird problems for some users.                                             
              |                                             
mar. 16 1995  | After some reports of hacked-up versions of the suite that
              | are supposed to float around, I've beefed up the security
              | in the program. During this I found two small bugs that got
              | fixed as well. I also added a <A NAME=""></A> tag after this
              | had been requested by some of the registered users...
              |                                             
mar. 18 1995  | Added 'DateStamp' menu item. When selecting this item, a date
              | stamp will be placed in your HTML document like the one below:
              | <I>Document last modified on: Sat Mar 18 11:57:47 1995.</I>            
              | The date and time used is that of your Amiga at the time when
              | the item is selected. As it's not a real tag, it's only in the                    
              | menu. But it has been given the Right-Amiga-] key-shortcut.
              |                                            
mar. 24 1995  | Added 'R'epeat gagdets to all the cycle gadgets in the HTML-
              | Wizard program. This to accomodate for the changed behaviour
              | of CycleToMenu 2.1.                        
              |                                            
apr.  5 1995  | Added a large number of character entities to the menu. So                                             
              | now you can easily create those special characters like the                                           
              | © sign, or ć or < and > and the likes. I've no idea if the                                            
              | AMosaic program supports these HTML+ entities. But the OS/2                                           
              | WebExplorer sure does. ;-) And most of the other mainstream                                           
              | browsers also do.  Also added Sub- and superscript tags.                                         
              |                                            
apr.  8 1995  | Added the brunt of the NetScape HTML extensions. As these
              | extensions are not standard HTML, they have been put in a                                           
              | seperate menu. Please note that not all browsers support                                           
              | these tags. Adding these tags to the program does not mean                                             
              | I agree or disagree with the NetScape people. It only states                                           
              | that I think users of teh suite may find these tags useful.                                           
              | Note: be careful with the Upper/Lowercase tooltype. As some                                           
              | of these tags are case-senstitive (eg. TYPE=I or TYPE=i)                                            
              |                                            
apr.  29 1995 | Fixed a stupid mistake that caused the programs to exit if in
